%T A393587 121,137,155,179,211,254,257,277,293,341,381,401,431,487,509,599,635,
%U A393587 661,773,907,961,1063,1297,1397,1418,1609,1621,1787,1913,2127,2293,2621,2749,3001,3469,3545,3637,3937
%N A393587 Matula-Goebel numbers of two-leaf rooted trees.
%C A393587 Each positive integer n corresponds to a unique rooted tree via the Matula-Goebel correspondence.
%C A393587 If an integer k belongs to the sequence, the prime number with index k is also a member of the sequence.
%C A393587 Any element of the sequence is obtained by applying a finite iteration of prime(-) to the product of two elements of A007097 together: the sequence is the three-dimensional array {prime^k(A007097(b)*A007097(c)), k>=0, b>=1, c>=1} arranged in increasing order.
%H A393587 Michel Marcus, <a href="/A393587/b393587.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..311</a>
%H A393587 Zizhen Chen, <a href="https://s2.smu.edu/~zizhenc/Project/MatulaNumber/">Matula number generator</a>.
%H A393587 Sean A. Irvine, <a href="https://github.com/archmageirvine/joeis/blob/master/src/irvine/oeis/a393/A393587.java">Java program</a> (github)
%H A393587 Dominique Manchon, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2602.03150">Une remarque sur l'arborification de Matula</a>, arXiv:2602.03150 [math.NT], 2026, see p. 6.
%H A393587 Dominique Manchon, <a href="https://hal.science/hal-05493935">Une remarque sur l'arborification de Matula</a>, hal-05493935, 2026, see p. 6.
%H A393587 D. W. Matula, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/2027327">A natural rooted tree enumeration by prime factorization</a>, SIAM Rev. vol. 10, 1968, p. 273.
%e A393587 a(1) = 4 = 2*2, the Matula-Goebel number of the V-shaped tree [..] with three vertices and one root.
%e A393587 a(2) = 6 = 2*3 = 2*prime(2), the Matula-Goebel number of the four-vertex rooted tree[[.].] obtained by grafting the forest [.]. on a common root.
%e A393587 a(3) = 7 = prime(4), the Matula-Goebel number of the Y-shaped tree [[..]].
%e A393587 a(17) = 59 = prime^3(4), the Matula-Goebel number of the tall Y-shaped tree [[[[..]]]].
%o A393587 (PARI) lista(nn) = my(list1 = List(), k=1); while(k<nn, k = prime(k); if (k<nn, listput(list1, k))); my(s = select(x->(x<nn), setbinop((x,y)->x*y, Vec(list1))), list = List());while(#s, for (i=1, #s, listput(list, s[i])); s = select(x->(x<nn), apply(prime, s));); Vec(vecsort(list)); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Mar 13 2026
%Y A393587 Cf. A007097 (Matula-Goebel numbers of one-leaf rooted trees).
